mages of Earth for three days. Zond 8 reached the Moon without any apparent problems, circling its target on 24 October at a range of {{convert|1110|km}} and took both [[black-and-white]] and [[Color photography|color photographs]] of the lunar surface during two separate sessions.<ref name=\"Experiment\">{{cite web|title=Zond 8: Experiments 1970-088A |url=https://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/nmc/spacecraft/displayExperiment.action?spacecraftId=1970-088A|website=nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov|publisher=NASA|date=27 February 2020|accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref> Scientific measurements were also obtained during the flight.<ref name=\"Deep Space\">{{cite web|last1=Siddiqi|first1=Asif A.|title=Beyond Earth: A Chronicle of Deep Space Exploration, 1958\u20132016|url=https://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/atoms/files/beyond-earth-tagged.pdf|publisher=NASA|date=2018}}</ref>\n\nAfter two mid-course corrections on the return leg, Zond 8 achieved a return trajectory over Earth's northern hemisphere instead of the standard southern approach profile, allowing Soviet ground control stations to maintain near-continuous contact with the craft. The guidance system, however, malfunctioned on the return leg, and the spacecraft performed a simple ballistic (instead of a guided) reentry into Earth's atmosphere.<ref name=\"Deep Space\"/>\n\nZond 8 descent module reentered the Earth's atmosphere and splashed down safely in the Indian Ocean at 13:55 GMT on 27 October 1970 at {{convert|730|km}} southeast of the Chagos Islands, {{convert|24|km}} from its original target point. The USSR recovery ship ''Taman'' was on hand to collect it and bring it back to Moscow.<ref name=\"Deep Space\"/>\n\n===Scientific instruments===\n* Imaging system\n* Solar wind collector packages\n\n==Zond 9==\nZond 9, Soyuz 7K-L1 s/n 10, was planned but cancelled. Zond 9 was planned to launch on July of 1969, carrying a crew of [[Pavel Popovich]] and [[Vitali Sevastyanov]], but never flew.<ref>[https://slideplayer.com/slide/12123170/ Soviet Manned Lunar Exploration Program]</ref>\n\n==Zond 10==\nZond 10, Soyuz 7K-L1 s/n 15, was planned but cancelled.<ref>[https://www.globalsecurity.org/space/world/russia/lunar-l-1.htm globalsecurity.org L-1 Lunar Circumnavigation Mission]</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Spaceflight}}\n\n* [[Splashdown (spacecraft landing)]]\n* [[Timeline of artificial satellites and space probes]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.mentallandscape.com/C_CatalogMoon.htm Soviet Lunar Images]\n* [https://archive.today/20120719105138/http://www.astronautix.com/craft/soyz7kl1.htm Astronautix.com - detailed on Soyuz 7K-L1 (Zond) program ]\n* {{APOD |date=16 July 2013 |title=The Moon from Zond 8}}\n\n{{Zond program}}\n{{Moon spacecraft}}\n{{N1-L3}}\n{{Orbital launches in 1970}}\n\n[[Category:Missions to the Moon]]\n[[Category:Zond program]]\n[[Category:1970 in the Soviet Union]]\n[[Category:Spacecraft launched in 1970]]\n[[Category:Spacecraft which reentered in 1970]]\n[[Category:Lunar flybys]]\n", "name_user": "CRS-20", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zond_8"}
{"title_page": "AVR (2020 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 film by Arindam Sharma}}\n{{EngvarB|date = April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = AVR\n| image          = [[File:Poster_Of_AVR_Assamese_Film.jpg|thumb|right|Poster of AVR]]\n| director       = [[Arindam Sharma]]\n| producer       = Brojen Sharma\n| writer         = Arindam Sharma\n| starring       = {{unbulleted list|[[Arnab Ayan]]|[[Ajay Barman]]|Niha Rani Das|Bikash Das|Nilutpal Borah}}\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Kailash Duarah\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2020|10|23|}}\n| country        = India\n| language       = Assamese\n| studio         = KrishnaKraft Production\n}}\n'''''AVR (Advik Vs. Ray)''''' is a 2020 upcoming [[India]]n [[Assamese cinema|Assamese-language]] [[Super Hero|Science Fiction]] [[Action film|action]] film directed by [[Arindam Sharma]] and starring [[Arnab Ayan]] and [[Niha Rani Das]] in the lead roles and [[Ajay Barman]] in lead villain.\n\nThe film release on 23 Oct 2020.\n\n== Cast ==\n\n* Arnab Ayan as Advik,Pranay\n* [[Ajay Barman]] as Ray, Dr.Roy\n* Niha Rani Das as Sneha (Pranay's Wife)\n* Bikash Das as Pratik (Pranay's Brother)\n* Nilutpal Borah as Bill (Pranay's Friend)\n\n== References ==\n\n1. {{Cite web|url=https://rupaliparda.com/archives/12430|title=\u0986\u09b9\u09bf \u0986\u099b\u09c7 \"AVR: Advik Vs Ray\"- \u098f\u0996\u09a8 \u0985\u09b8\u09ae\u09c0\u09af\u09bc\u09be \"\u099a\u09c1\u09aa\u09be\u09f0\u09b9\u09bf\u09f0\u09cb\" \u099b\u09ac\u09bf\u0983|website=rupaliparda.com}}\n\n2.{{Cite web|url=https://assamtimespost.com/?p=17846|title=\u0986\u09b9\u09bf \u0986\u099b\u09c7 \u0985\u09b8\u09ae\u09c0\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09a4 \u098f\u0996\u09a8 \u201c\u099a\u09c1\u09aa\u09be\u09f0\u09b9\u09bf\u09f0\u09cb\u2019 \u099a\u09bf\u09a8\u09c7\u09ae\u09be\"\u0964 \u09a8\u09f1\u09be\u0997\u09a4 \u09aa\u09f0\u09bf\u099a\u09be\u09b2\u0995 \u0985\u09f0\u09bf\u09a8\u09cd\u09a6\u09ae \u09b6\u09f0\u09cd\u09ae\u09be\u09f0 \u09aa\u09f0\u09bf\u